Abstract: In this paper, our motivation is to present new methods for testing the goodness-of-fit of linear or nonlinear regression or autoregression functions for parametric models of order 1, under stationarity and ergodicity assumptions. Our basic procedure is based on a measure of the cumulated deviation process ^ A n () between a weighted process of residuals and a parametric estimator of the cumulated conditional mean function (i.e. regression or autoregression function), under the null hypothesis H 0 . Neither the conditional variance function nor the distribution of the noise or the stationary distribution of the observations is assumed known. In this part (1), we essentially establish a functional limit theorem (Theorem 2) for the process of deviations between the weighted process of residuals under consideration and its parametric counterpart, under H 0 . We also establish a simpler functional limit theorem (Theorem 3) for a variant of the process ^ A n (). The proof of these results is based on a general functional limit theorem (Theorem 1) for a class of multivariate martingale difference arrays. Several tests can be based on these results. It is possible to use them when the conditional variance function, the distribution of the noise and the stationary distribution of the observations are all unknown. A precise description of these tests together with estimation matters, as well as the examination of their asymptotic power, are postponed to part (2) of this paper. 
